   <text type="letter">
      <body>
         <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02115.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
         <opener rend="right">
            <dateline>
               <name type="place">Washington,</name>
               <date when="1866-11-26">26 November, 1866.</date>
            </dateline>
            <salute>My dear Whitman, </salute>
         </opener>
         <p>I rec<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> this morning from an old friend (Mr. Robert
               Buchanan)<ptr target="loc.04207_n1"/> in England a letter and among other things he
            asks me to send him "Leaves of Grass, Drum Taps and any other works by the author Walt
            Whitman of the Attorney General's Department, Washington, and a portrait if it is to be
            got by hook or crook. I shall make a copy from each negative. Please tell me if there
            are any other works of yours than the above &amp; where I can get them. He desires also
            that I should send him a portrait of Emerson&#8212;Can you tell me where I can get a
            good one</p>
         <closer rend="right">
            <salute>Yours respectfully,</salute>
            <signed>Alex. Gardner.</signed>
         </closer>
